    "comment": "Rationale: Impaired NMDAR-dependent plasticity at Sch-CA1 synapses in AIDA-1 cKO mice (Fig. 6). Altered GluN2A-mediated and GluN2B-mediated synaptic transmission and synaptic expression in AIDA-1 cKO mice (Fig. 4).\n\n6/9/2017 Pim\n- Since the AIDA-1 protein is preferentially localized in the PSD, the regulation of synaptic transmission and LTP induction is annotated by SynGO.. Experimental description: To generate forebrain-specific AIDA-1 cKO mice, we crossed AIDA-1(fl/fl) mice with previously characterized CaMKII-Cre transgenic mice (p. 8987)",
